sentences: Jason René Castro (born March 25, 1987) is an American acoustic/folk-pop singer, songwriter, and real estate agent.
After Idol, he signed a recording contract with Atlantic Records, and his self-titled debut album was released on April 13, 2010.
Early years ==
He received a 1340 out of 1600 on his SAT.

Castro has sported dreadlocks since his senior year of high school.
In 2014, symbolic of a spiritual reawakening, he cut his dreadlocks and has since worn his hair much shorter.

During a March 17, 2008 appearance on The Oprah Winfrey Show, judge Simon Cowell chose Castro as one of his four favorites in the competition, along with David Cook, David Archuleta, and Brooke White.

On April 12, Ryan Seacrest and the three judges appeared in Larry King Live, Larry King revealed the results of his website poll which asked "Whom do you want to win American Idol?" and said that Castro was in the lead.

He was voted off the competition on May 7, 2008.
Buckley's version of the song sold 178,000 digital downloads in the week following Castro's performance, to debut at number one on Billboard's Hot Digital Songs chart.
According to the March 22, 2008, issue of Billboard, this was the highest boost in digital sales a song had ever received after being performed by a contestant on American Idol.
Jason Castro's rendition of the song propelled Jeff Buckley's version to be certified gold and platinum as a single on April 22, 2008.
After his elimination Castro made a number of television appearances including on The Tonight Show with Jay Leno and The Ellen DeGeneres Show
